  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4</p><p>Peel the <strong>potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and chop into very small pieces</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1580806868301-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1580806868301-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1580806868301-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1580806868301-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1580806868301-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> to one side of a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle and set some <strong>butter </strong>aside near a warm place to get to room temperature for easy spreading later on</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580806960320-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580806960320-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580806960320-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580806960320-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580806960320-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to a large pot with a lid over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the onions are beginning to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong> and cook for 1-2 min further</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580806964121-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580806964121-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580806964121-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580806964121-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580806964121-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>vegetable stock mix<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into the pan and add 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a medium-high heat and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Slice the <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> thin slices</p><p>Slice the <strong>ciabattas </strong>in half and <strong>butter </strong>both bases</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580806967931-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580806967931-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580806967931-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580806967931-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580806967931-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the oven</p><p>Add one rasher of <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> to each ciabatta base (save the remaining rashers for later) and layer 4 <strong>cheese slices</strong> on top</p><p>Add both the <strong>ciabatta</strong> <strong>bases</strong> and <strong>lids</strong> (cut side up) to the other side of the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 5-6 min or until the cheese has melted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
